The archetypal '''action hero''' or heroine is the protagonist of an [[action film]] or other entertainment which portrays action and adventure.<ref>{{citation |title=Blood, guns, and testosterone: action films, audiences, and a thirst for violence |author=Barna William Donovan |publisher=Scarecrow Press |year=2010 |isbn=9780810872622}}</ref>  Other media in which such heroes appear include [[swashbuckler film]]s, [[Westerns on television]], [[old-time radio]], [[adventure novel]]s, [[dime novel]]s, [[pulp magazine]]s, and [[folklore]].

