'''Bu-Ba-Bu''' is a literary performance group started by three [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] writers [[Yuri Andrukhovych]], [[Viktor Neborak]], and [[Oleksandr Irvanets]].  The group was founded in April 1985 in [[L'viv]].  The group's three syllables stand for "burlesque, balagan, and buffonada".<ref> [http://www.rochester.edu/College/translation/threepercent/index.php?id=9772 Ukraine: Everybody's Business]</ref> The idea behind the groups formation was in order to present a carnival like interpretation of events in Ukraine.

