'''Jeepney TV''' is a [[Philippine]] [[pay television]] channel owned by [[Creative Programs]], a subsidiary of the media conglomerate [[ABS-CBN|ABS-CBN Corporation]]. Its programming consists of classic and archived series previously aired on [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]. It is named after the [[jeepney]], an automotive vehicle that has been widely used as a mode of transportation in the Philippines since World War II.<ref>[http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/10/17/12/new-cable-channel-re-air-classic-abs-cbn-shows New cable channel to re-air classic ABS-CBN shows] retrieved via www.abscbnnews.com 10-18-2012</ref>
On 27 November 2015, Jeepney TV revamped its graphics and program line-up, and the programming scheduled was overhauled yet again in June 2018.
From 30 July to 31 December 2018, Jeepney TV is available on [[ABS-CBN TV Plus]] as a free trial channel, together with [[O Shopping]], [[Asianovela Channel]], [[Movie Central (Philippines)|Movie Central]] and [[Myx]].
